This series of scripts takes the data outputted directly from the scanner and reshapes into a format appropriate for BIDS conversion. 

Data checking must happen first, following these rules:
	a) Make sure nothing's missing from the full expected dataset 
	b) Check for which files are present and check against the log for what happened during the scan to see if they match or if any are 
     missing from the upload, make a note if missing 
	c) Check for file duplicates (look at every image and output in order to check this)
		i) take the later scan if there are two of a particular run 
		ii) take the longer one if they're longer
		iii) check against the task files to see if participants just weren't responding or if there's some other obvious reason like the 
         wrong playlist was used for a particular run

These checks are recorded in a master inventory sheet of all scans on the SLaM sharepoint, where there is records of each participant who 
took part and notes on how their scans went. Once the data has been checked, files chosen from duplicates if there are any doubles (or 
triples), then file reshaping can take place. 

The main aims of the reshape folder scripts are then:
- To rename all files into a consistent format
- To move all files into appropriate folders by type of data (i.e. scan image, behavioural output, physiology recordings)
- To make behavioural output from button pressing more readable, and more easily inputted to SPM at the analysis stage

Once data is in appropriate folders, BIDS conversion can be undertaken. This requires a configuriation file that explains the content of 
each scan which will be converted. At this stage, zipped nifti files are generated. Without a config file, fmriprep will not run. No 
behavioural data is needed at this stage, but participant information must also be input to a bare-bones level in a BIDS required file.
